        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#VM">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name>Πανχάρεός</name></persName> εἰμι
                    <lb n="2"/>καὶ το͂ν φίλο̄ν ϙοινά εἰμι
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note>Text after Arena 1989 (IGASM I)</note>
                    </app>
                    <app>
                        <note>Orlandini, Jeffery, Dubois: Παντάρεος</note>
                    </app>
                    <app>
                        <note>Lazzarini: Πανχάρεος</note>
                    </app>
                    <app>
                        <note>Arena 1989: the iota of καὶ was initially omitted and was added in a later stage.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#VM">
                <p>I am (the cup) of Panchares, and I am shared among (his) friends.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#VM">
                <p>Sono (la coppa) di Panchares, e sono condivisa tra i (suoi) amici.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>The inscription is written, according to Arena (1986) in the Megarian alphabet but was found in Gela. According to Jeffery (1961) 
                    the object may have ended up in Gela following the events that caused the conquest of Megara by Syracuse. It should be noted that the name Πανχάρες is recurrent in Megara Nisea, 
                    as Arena (1989) points out reporting parallels with IG VII 1-11, 12, 13, 42 and IG IV 926 (= IG IV 1[2] 71), and occurrs once in Akraiphia, Boeotia (IG VII 2750).
                    The text, which denounces the name of its possessor, refers to its use during symposia.</p>
                <!-- Jeffery Archive: J.WC. Gela 50 p.01.(6) -->
            </div>
